Dimension: Performance & Complexity / Testability

Location: src/proxy.rs lines 621-630 (compactor cloning in proxy_chat_completions).

Violation:
  let mut compactor = crate::compaction::ContextCompactor::for_model(&request.model);
  let base_config = state.compactor.config().clone();
  let mut model_config = compactor.config().clone();
  model_config.preserve_recent = base_config.preserve_recent;
  model_config.preserve_system = base_config.preserve_system;
  model_config.preserve_tool_calls = base_config.preserve_tool_calls;
  compactor.set_config(model_config);

This clones TWO CompactionConfig objects on every single request just to override three fields from state.compactor into a fresh model-specific compactor. The shared state.compactor in ProxyState (line 55) is itself misleading — it holds only the config the user set, but is then thrown away per-request in favor of a model-specific one. The result is:
  (a) `state.compactor` in ProxyState is effectively a config container, not a reusable compactor. Misleading type.
  (b) Two allocations per request.
  (c) Hard to test: the three fields that are 'forwarded' are implicit — a new CompactionConfig field added (e.g., 'summary_style') would NOT be propagated and would silently use the model-specific default.

Mandated Refactor:
  1. Change ProxyState::compactor from ContextCompactor to CompactionConfig (or CompactionOverrides struct). Document it as 'user-provided overrides'.
  2. Add `impl ContextCompactor { pub fn for_model_with_overrides(model: &str, overrides: &CompactionOverrides) -> Self }` that applies the overrides declaratively — struct-update syntax `{ ..model_defaults, ..overrides }` (requires overrides to be a distinct type or Option<...> fields).
  3. Use a `#[derive(Debug, Clone, Default)]` Overrides struct with Option fields so that a None means 'use model default'. This makes the three-field forwarding explicit.
  4. proxy_chat_completions then: `let compactor = ContextCompactor::for_model_with_overrides(&request.model, &state.compactor_overrides);` — one line, no clones, and if a new CompactionConfig field is added, the Overrides struct forces a decision at compile time.
